---
title: Welcome
layout: home.njk
description: A clean, bootstrap-like blog/portfolio starter.
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container hero-inner">
    <h1 class="page-title">{{ site.title }}</h1>
    <p class="lead">A simple blog/portfolio starter with a clean, readable layout.</p>
  </div>
  
</section>

<section class="container content mt-6">
  <h2 class="mt-0">Hello, I’m Marko</h2>
  <p class="lead">This is a fake homepage to showcase the theme. It includes a visible site title, a navigation menu, a page title, and a centered content column.</p>
  <p>Use this space to introduce yourself or your project. Replace the text with a short bio, your focus areas, or links to featured work. Keep paragraphs concise for readability.</p>
  <p>Looking for a contact page? You’ll find it in the header. You can also add posts and projects as your content grows.</p>
</section>

<section class="container content mt-6">
  <h2 class="mt-0">Latest Posts</h2>
  <div class="cards mt-4">
    {% for post in collections.posts | reverse | slice(0, 4) %}
      <article class="card">
        <h3><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
        {% if post.date %}
        <p class="meta"><time>{{ post.date }}</time></p>
        {% endif %}
        <p>{{ post.data.description or (post.templateContent | excerpt(24)) }}</p>
        <a class="more" href="{{ post.url }}">Read more →</a>
      </article>
    {% else %}
      <p>No posts yet. Create one with <code>npm run new:post -- --title "My First Post"</code>.</p>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p class="mt-4"><a href="{{ '/posts/' | i18nPath(lang) }}">View all posts →</a></p>
</section>
